		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Quick question about DRAM</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The palettes and sprite OAM are DRAM, right? Meaning the values will fade out if not touched for a while?
<br />
<br />When rendering is on, is the access the PPU performs to read those values enough to keep them alive?
<br />
<br />My real question is: if I don't update the palette for a while, will it degrade? Will the colors (palette entries) I don't use degrade?

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

	<table width="85%" cellspacing="3" cellpadding="0" border="0" align="center">
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Author:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Bregalad</b> [ Mon May 08, 2006 11:52 am ]</td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />No, as long as you keep the screen on.
<br />If you turn the screen on for about one frame, palette RAM risk to degrade. If you do for about 2 frames, OAM will too. As long as the screen is on there is no problem.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


